                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.77/135</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-12T14:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 11, 4 p.m. Minister of Foreign Affairs states information, not
                    instructions, with reference to National Railroad asked for by Minister Ménos is
                    being prepared by Department of Public Works and will be forwarded at the
                    earliest possible moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
